<TITLE> Khaleda visits 2 more families </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 8 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition leader Khaleda Zia Sunday met with families of two army officers killed in the Feb. 25-26 BDR mutiny. The BNP chief conveyed her sympathy to the families of Col Md Aftabul Islam and Col Zahid Hossain at Uttara sectors 7 and 6. The families demanded punishment to the perpetrators of the massacre. In last few days, Khaleda met seven bereaved families. At least 55 army officers have been killed or missing in the mutiny. She also met with the family of Tareq Aziz, a private university student, one of the three civilians killed in the mutiny. bdnew
